NEWLY crowned Miss Universe Zozi reflects on being both Miss SA and Miss Universe in 2019. She said a door was opened and she could not be more grateful. MISS SA IS NOT HAPPY IN NEW YORK  Zozibini was crowned in the early hours of Monday at a glamorous ceremony in Atlanta, USA.  The 25-year-old BTech student and striking beauty from the Eastern Cape was part of top 20 girls who have been voted for by the public. MISS SA RESPONDS TO NEGATIVE COMMENTS ABOUT HER BLACKNESS  Zozibini is the third Mzansi girl to win the Miss Universe crown, after Margaret Gardiner in 1978, and Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters in 2017.     